The dates of these two works are mutually dependent, and therefore they must be considered together. This, he says, was written ‘ante quinquennium.' Ib. 145. And he begs that his defence may be read ‘coram uenerabili Domino . . . Wilfrido antistite.' Both these dates, viz. the fifth year of Tiberius and the date 703 A. D., occur in c. 14 of the work, Opp. vi. 130, a passage which seems to have been over- looked. This, then, is the date of the De Temporibus, and the Letter to Plegwin is fixed to 708.
